  "texts": [
    "Note that the original PAC-Bayes bounds do not allow to take a data-dependent prior.",
    "Thus, some additional work is required to make this possible (e.g the union bound on σ 2 by Dziugaite and Roy (2017) discussed above).",
    "The first occurence of this idea is due to Seeger (2003, Chapter 4).",
    "Seeger proposed to split the sample in two parts.",
    "The first part is used to define Θ and the prior π, and the PAC-Bayes bound is applied on the second part of the sample (that is, conditionally on the first part)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "The first occurence of this idea is due to Seeger (2003, Chapter 4)."
  ]
}